import React from 'react'; import { Container, Typography, Box, Grid, Paper, Divider } from '@mui/material'; function About() { return ( About NeuroAI Revolutionizing medical training with cutting-edge AI technology {gridItems.map((item, index) => ( {item.title} {item.description} ))} {/* New Section: Read the Curriculum */} Read the Curriculum Explore our comprehensive curriculum designed to equip you with the latest knowledge and skills in neurology. Our curriculum is tailored to meet the needs of medical professionals at all levels, from beginners to experts. {/* Curriculum Guide Section */} Curriculum Guide Week 1: Neurosurgery and AI in MRI Analysis Morning (Clinics): Neurosurgery clinic exposure as planned. Afternoon (Case Identification and AI Integration):
  • AI Tool Integration: Introduce residents to AI tools such as Aidoc and Zebra Medical Vision for MRI analysis.
  • Hands-on Training: Residents will perform MRI reviews using Aidoc and Zebra Medical Vision to detect abnormalities.
  • Objective: Understand the role of AI in improving speed and accuracy in MRI interpretation.
 Week 2: Genetics and AI in Genomic Evaluation Morning (Clinics): Genetics clinics as planned. Afternoon (Case Identification and AI Integration):
  • AI Tool Integration: Residents will be introduced to AI tools like DeepVariant, Fabric Genomics, and Illumina DRAGEN Bio-IT Platform.
  • Hands-on Training: Residents will be given patient genetic data to run through platforms like DeepVariant and Fabric Genomics.
  • Objective: Learn how AI streamlines genomic evaluation and improves the accuracy of diagnosing genetic disorders.
 Week 3: Neurology and Neuroradiology – AI in EEG and MRI Morning (Clinics): Neurology and neuroradiology clinics as planned. Afternoon (Case Identification and AI Integration):
  • EEG AI Tools: Introduce residents to Persyst EEG Analysis Software, Epilog, and Nervive.
  • Hands-on Training: Residents will run EEG recordings through Persyst and Nervive.
  • Objective: Understand the potential of AI in real-time EEG interpretation.
  • MRI AI Tools: Continue using AI tools from Week 1 for neuroradiology cases.
 Week 4: Case Synthesis and Presentation Morning (Clinics): Continuation of clinic participation. Afternoon (Case Review and Presentation Preparation):
  • Case Pooling: Residents will choose 4 representative cases.
  • Pediatric Grand Rounds Presentation: The presentation will highlight key cases and AI integration.
  • Objective: Demonstrate the ability to integrate AI tools into clinical workflows.
 Additional Resources for Self-Learning
  • Online Modules: Access to online learning modules and tutorials.
  • Mentor-Led Workshops: Weekly seminars with specialists.
